{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":936,"text":"Chris Anderson: So, Jon, this feels scary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":3160,"text":"Jonathan Haidt: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":4349,"text":"CA: It feels like the world is in a place"},{"time":6363,"text":"that we haven't seen for a long time."},{"time":8224,"text":"People don't just disagree\nin the way that we're familiar with,"},{"time":12809,"text":"on the left-right political divide."},{"time":14733,"text":"There are much deeper differences afoot."},{"time":17758,"text":"What on earth is going on,\nand how did we get here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":21048,"text":"JH: This is different."},{"time":24075,"text":"There's a much more\napocalyptic sort of feeling."},{"time":27326,"text":"Survey research by Pew Research shows"},{"time":29676,"text":"that the degree to which we feel\nthat the other side is not just --"},{"time":33409,"text":"we don't just dislike them;\nwe strongly dislike them,"},{"time":36407,"text":"and we think that they are\na threat to the nation."},{"time":39907,"text":"Those numbers have been going up and up,"},{"time":41895,"text":"and those are over 50 percent\nnow on both sides."},{"time":44656,"text":"People are scared,"},{"time":45831,"text":"because it feels like this is different\nthan before; it's much more intense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49482,"text":"Whenever I look\nat any sort of social puzzle,"},{"time":52026,"text":"I always apply the three basic\nprinciples of moral psychology,"},{"time":55167,"text":"and I think they'll help us here."},{"time":57085,"text":"So the first thing that you\nhave to always keep in mind"},{"time":59842,"text":"when you're thinking about politics"},{"time":61602,"text":"is that we're tribal."},{"time":63006,"text":"We evolved for tribalism."},{"time":64553,"text":"One of the simplest and greatest\ninsights into human social nature"},{"time":67746,"text":"is the Bedouin proverb:"},{"time":68943,"text":"\"Me against my brother;"},{"time":70359,"text":"me and my brother against our cousin;"},{"time":72310,"text":"me and my brother and cousins\nagainst the stranger.\""},{"time":74836,"text":"And that tribalism allowed us\nto create large societies"},{"time":79584,"text":"and to come together\nin order to compete with others."},{"time":82640,"text":"That brought us out of the jungle\nand out of small groups,"},{"time":86345,"text":"but it means that we have\neternal conflict."},{"time":88392,"text":"The question you have to look at is:"},{"time":90157,"text":"What aspects of our society\nare making that more bitter,"},{"time":92845,"text":"and what are calming them down?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":94399,"text":"CA: That's a very dark proverb."},{"time":95984,"text":"You're saying that that's actually\nbaked into most people's mental wiring"},{"time":100181,"text":"at some level?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":101356,"text":"JH: Oh, absolutely. This is just\na basic aspect of human social cognition."},{"time":105184,"text":"But we can also live together\nreally peacefully,"},{"time":107531,"text":"and we've invented all kinds\nof fun ways of, like, playing war."},{"time":110950,"text":"I mean, sports, politics --"},{"time":112356,"text":"these are all ways that we get\nto exercise this tribal nature"},{"time":116075,"text":"without actually hurting anyone."},{"time":117682,"text":"We're also really good at trade\nand exploration and meeting new people."},{"time":122051,"text":"So you have to see our tribalism\nas something that goes up or down --"},{"time":125374,"text":"it's not like we're doomed\nto always be fighting each other,"},{"time":128250,"text":"but we'll never have world peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":130980,"text":"CA: The size of that tribe\ncan shrink or expand."}]},{"cues":[{"time":134226,"text":"JH: Right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":135401,"text":"CA: The size of what we consider \"us\""},{"time":137412,"text":"and what we consider \"other\" or \"them\""},{"time":139857,"text":"can change."},{"time":142610,"text":"And some people believed that process\ncould continue indefinitely."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148224,"text":"JH: That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":149440,"text":"CA: And we were indeed expanding\nthe sense of tribe for a while."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152670,"text":"JH: So this is, I think,"},{"time":153855,"text":"where we're getting at what's possibly\nthe new left-right distinction."},{"time":157234,"text":"I mean, the left-right\nas we've all inherited it,"},{"time":159581,"text":"comes out of the labor\nversus capital distinction,"},{"time":162444,"text":"and the working class, and Marx."},{"time":164843,"text":"But I think what we're seeing\nnow, increasingly,"},{"time":167116,"text":"is a divide in all the Western democracies"},{"time":169994,"text":"between the people\nwho want to stop at nation,"},{"time":173725,"text":"the people who are more parochial --"},{"time":175499,"text":"and I don't mean that in a bad way --"},{"time":177320,"text":"people who have much more\nof a sense of being rooted,"},{"time":180144,"text":"they care about their town,\ntheir community and their nation."},{"time":183824,"text":"And then those who are\nanti-parochial and who --"},{"time":187885,"text":"whenever I get confused, I just think\nof the John Lennon song \"Imagine.\""},{"time":191309,"text":"\"Imagine there's no countries,\nnothing to kill or die for.\""},{"time":194162,"text":"And so these are the people\nwho want more global governance,"},{"time":197399,"text":"they don't like nation states,\nthey don't like borders."},{"time":200097,"text":"You see this all over Europe as well."},{"time":201946,"text":"There's a great metaphor guy --\nactually, his name is Shakespeare --"},{"time":205196,"text":"writing ten years ago in Britain."},{"time":206801,"text":"He had a metaphor:"},{"time":207992,"text":"\"Are we drawbridge-uppers\nor drawbridge-downers?\""},{"time":211289,"text":"And Britain is divided\n52-48 on that point."},{"time":214218,"text":"And America is divided on that point, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217379,"text":"CA: And so, those of us\nwho grew up with The Beatles"},{"time":220980,"text":"and that sort of hippie philosophy\nof dreaming of a more connected world --"},{"time":224578,"text":"it felt so idealistic and \"how could\nanyone think badly about that?\""},{"time":228736,"text":"And what you're saying is that, actually,"},{"time":230771,"text":"millions of people today\nfeel that that isn't just silly;"},{"time":235097,"text":"it's actually dangerous and wrong,\nand they're scared of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237982,"text":"JH: I think the big issue, especially\nin Europe but also here,"},{"time":241032,"text":"is the issue of immigration."},{"time":242423,"text":"And I think this is where\nwe have to look very carefully"},{"time":245516,"text":"at the social science\nabout diversity and immigration."},{"time":249171,"text":"Once something becomes politicized,"},{"time":250909,"text":"once it becomes something\nthat the left loves and the right --"},{"time":253957,"text":"then even the social scientists\ncan't think straight about it."},{"time":257082,"text":"Now, diversity is good in a lot of ways."},{"time":259063,"text":"It clearly creates more innovation."},{"time":261294,"text":"The American economy\nhas grown enormously from it."},{"time":263795,"text":"Diversity and immigration\ndo a lot of good things."},{"time":266201,"text":"But what the globalists,\nI think, don't see,"},{"time":268853,"text":"what they don't want to see,"},{"time":270384,"text":"is that ethnic diversity\ncuts social capital and trust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276686,"text":"There's a very important\nstudy by Robert Putnam,"},{"time":279046,"text":"the author of \"Bowling Alone,\""},{"time":280926,"text":"looking at social capital databases."},{"time":282805,"text":"And basically, the more people\nfeel that they are the same,"},{"time":285776,"text":"the more they trust each other,"},{"time":287307,"text":"the more they can have\na redistributionist welfare state."},{"time":290071,"text":"Scandinavian countries are so wonderful"},{"time":292066,"text":"because they have this legacy\nof being small, homogenous countries."},{"time":295439,"text":"And that leads to\na progressive welfare state,"},{"time":299180,"text":"a set of progressive\nleft-leaning values, which says,"},{"time":302007,"text":"\"Drawbridge down!\nThe world is a great place."},{"time":305032,"text":"People in Syria are suffering --\nwe must welcome them in.\""},{"time":308088,"text":"And it's a beautiful thing."},{"time":309934,"text":"But if, and I was in Sweden\nthis summer,"},{"time":312541,"text":"if the discourse in Sweden\nis fairly politically correct"},{"time":315748,"text":"and they can't talk about the downsides,"},{"time":318009,"text":"you end up bringing a lot of people in."},{"time":320020,"text":"That's going to cut social capital,"},{"time":321736,"text":"it makes it hard to have a welfare state"},{"time":323705,"text":"and they might end up,\nas we have in America,"},{"time":326285,"text":"with a racially divided, visibly\nracially divided, society."},{"time":329922,"text":"So this is all very\nuncomfortable to talk about."},{"time":332206,"text":"But I think this is the thing,\nespecially in Europe and for us, too,"},{"time":335475,"text":"we need to be looking at."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336692,"text":"CA: You're saying that people of reason,"},{"time":338802,"text":"people who would consider\nthemselves not racists,"},{"time":341314,"text":"but moral, upstanding people,"},{"time":343065,"text":"have a rationale that says\nhumans are just too different;"},{"time":346035,"text":"that we're in danger of overloading\nour sense of what humans are capable of,"},{"time":351498,"text":"by mixing in people who are too different."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354012,"text":"JH: Yes, but I can make it\nmuch more palatable"},{"time":357576,"text":"by saying it's not necessarily about race."},{"time":360819,"text":"It's about culture."},{"time":362110,"text":"There's wonderful work by a political\nscientist named Karen Stenner,"},{"time":366307,"text":"who shows that when people have a sense"},{"time":369558,"text":"that we are all united,\nwe're all the same,"},{"time":371817,"text":"there are many people who have\na predisposition to authoritarianism."},{"time":375091,"text":"Those people aren't particularly racist"},{"time":377157,"text":"when they feel as through\nthere's not a threat"},{"time":379348,"text":"to our social and moral order."},{"time":381071,"text":"But if you prime them experimentally"},{"time":383128,"text":"by thinking we're coming apart,\npeople are getting more different,"},{"time":386284,"text":"then they get more racist, homophobic,\nthey want to kick out the deviants."},{"time":389831,"text":"So it's in part that you get\nan authoritarian reaction."},{"time":392762,"text":"The left, following through\nthe Lennonist line --"},{"time":395123,"text":"the John Lennon line --"},{"time":396433,"text":"does things that create\nan authoritarian reaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":398866,"text":"We're certainly seeing that\nin America with the alt-right."},{"time":401685,"text":"We saw it in Britain,\nwe've seen it all over Europe."},{"time":404291,"text":"But the more positive part of that"},{"time":406897,"text":"is that I think the localists,\nor the nationalists, are actually right --"},{"time":411218,"text":"that, if you emphasize\nour cultural similarity,"},{"time":415029,"text":"then race doesn't actually\nmatter very much."},{"time":417280,"text":"So an assimilationist\napproach to immigration"},{"time":420012,"text":"removes a lot of these problems."},{"time":421593,"text":"And if you value having\na generous welfare state,"},{"time":424004,"text":"you've got to emphasize\nthat we're all the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426840,"text":"CA: OK, so rising immigration\nand fears about that"},{"time":429958,"text":"are one of the causes\nof the current divide."},{"time":433149,"text":"What are other causes?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":434886,"text":"JH: The next principle of moral psychology"},{"time":436931,"text":"is that intuitions come first,\nstrategic reasoning second."},{"time":440758,"text":"You've probably heard\nthe term \"motivated reasoning\""},{"time":443262,"text":"or \"confirmation bias.\""},{"time":444893,"text":"There's some really interesting work"},{"time":446834,"text":"on how our high intelligence\nand our verbal abilities"},{"time":449935,"text":"might have evolved\nnot to help us find out the truth,"},{"time":453161,"text":"but to help us manipulate each other,\ndefend our reputation ..."},{"time":456157,"text":"We're really, really good\nat justifying ourselves."},{"time":459147,"text":"And when you bring\ngroup interests into account,"},{"time":461538,"text":"so it's not just me,\nit's my team versus your team,"},{"time":464299,"text":"whereas if you're evaluating evidence\nthat your side is wrong,"},{"time":467236,"text":"we just can't accept that."},{"time":469017,"text":"So this is why you can't win\na political argument."},{"time":471758,"text":"If you're debating something,"},{"time":473275,"text":"you can't persuade the person\nwith reasons and evidence,"},{"time":476346,"text":"because that's not\nthe way reasoning works."},{"time":478715,"text":"So now, give us the internet,\ngive us Google:"},{"time":482522,"text":"\"I heard that Barack Obama\nwas born in Kenya."},{"time":485276,"text":"Let me Google that -- oh my God!\n10 million hits! Look, he was!\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":489248,"text":"CA: So this has come as an unpleasant\nsurprise to a lot of people."},{"time":492412,"text":"Social media has often been framed\nby techno-optimists"},{"time":495284,"text":"as this great connecting force\nthat would bring people together."},{"time":500555,"text":"And there have been some\nunexpected counter-effects to that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":504922,"text":"JH: That's right."},{"time":506097,"text":"That's why I'm very enamored\nof yin-yang views"},{"time":508502,"text":"of human nature and left-right --"},{"time":510144,"text":"that each side is right\nabout certain things,"},{"time":512634,"text":"but then it goes blind to other things."},{"time":514779,"text":"And so the left generally believes\nthat human nature is good:"},{"time":517781,"text":"bring people together, knock down\nthe walls and all will be well."},{"time":520970,"text":"The right -- social conservatives,\nnot libertarians --"},{"time":523552,"text":"social conservatives generally\nbelieve people can be greedy"},{"time":527829,"text":"and sexual and selfish,"},{"time":529235,"text":"and we need regulation,\nand we need restrictions."},{"time":532214,"text":"So, yeah, if you knock down all the walls,"},{"time":534640,"text":"allow people to communicate\nall over the world,"},{"time":536893,"text":"you get a lot of porn and a lot of racism."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538975,"text":"CA: So help us understand."},{"time":540260,"text":"These principles of human nature\nhave been with us forever."},{"time":546918,"text":"What's changed that's deepened\nthis feeling of division?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":552360,"text":"JH: You have to see six to ten\ndifferent threads all coming together."},{"time":557373,"text":"I'll just list a couple of them."},{"time":559398,"text":"So in America, one of the big --\nactually, America and Europe --"},{"time":563900,"text":"one of the biggest ones is World War II."},{"time":565837,"text":"There's interesting research\nfrom Joe Henrich and others"},{"time":568504,"text":"that says if your country was at war,"},{"time":570931,"text":"especially when you were young,"},{"time":572512,"text":"then we test you 30 years later\nin a commons dilemma"},{"time":575650,"text":"or a prisoner's dilemma,"},{"time":577003,"text":"you're more cooperative."},{"time":578983,"text":"Because of our tribal nature, if you're --"},{"time":581880,"text":"my parents were teenagers\nduring World War II,"},{"time":584821,"text":"and they would go out\nlooking for scraps of aluminum"},{"time":587406,"text":"to help the war effort."},{"time":588619,"text":"I mean, everybody pulled together."},{"time":590821,"text":"And so then these people go on,"},{"time":592374,"text":"they rise up through business\nand government,"},{"time":594796,"text":"they take leadership positions."},{"time":596451,"text":"They're really good\nat compromise and cooperation."},{"time":599726,"text":"They all retire by the '90s."},{"time":601685,"text":"So we're left with baby boomers\nby the end of the '90s."},{"time":605010,"text":"And their youth was spent fighting\neach other within each country,"},{"time":609001,"text":"in 1968 and afterwards."},{"time":610672,"text":"The loss of the World War II generation,\n\"The Greatest Generation,\""},{"time":614690,"text":"is huge."},{"time":616567,"text":"So that's one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618440,"text":"Another, in America,\nis the purification of the two parties."},{"time":621949,"text":"There used to be liberal Republicans\nand conservative Democrats."},{"time":625020,"text":"So America had a mid-20th century\nthat was really bipartisan."},{"time":628211,"text":"But because of a variety of factors\nthat started things moving,"},{"time":632602,"text":"by the 90's, we had a purified\nliberal party and conservative party."},{"time":636024,"text":"So now, the people in either party\nreally are different,"},{"time":638693,"text":"and we really don't want\nour children to marry them,"},{"time":641200,"text":"which, in the '60s,\ndidn't matter very much."},{"time":643292,"text":"So, the purification of the parties."},{"time":645113,"text":"Third is the internet and, as I said,"},{"time":647609,"text":"it's just the most amazing stimulant\nfor post-hoc reasoning and demonization."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652316,"text":"CA: The tone of what's happening\non the internet now is quite troubling."},{"time":657132,"text":"I just did a quick search\non Twitter about the election"},{"time":660003,"text":"and saw two tweets next to each other."},{"time":663335,"text":"One, against a picture of racist graffiti:"},{"time":668007,"text":"\"This is disgusting!"},{"time":669664,"text":"Ugliness in this country,\nbrought to us by #Trump.\""},{"time":673424,"text":"And then the next one is:"},{"time":675339,"text":"\"Crooked Hillary\ndedication page. Disgusting!\""},{"time":679176,"text":"So this idea of \"disgust\"\nis troubling to me."},{"time":683407,"text":"Because you can have an argument\nor a disagreement about something,"},{"time":686666,"text":"you can get angry at someone."},{"time":689094,"text":"Disgust, I've heard you say,\ntakes things to a much deeper level."}]},{"cues":[{"time":692711,"text":"JH: That's right. Disgust is different."},{"time":694622,"text":"Anger -- you know, I have kids."},{"time":696609,"text":"They fight 10 times a day,"},{"time":698383,"text":"and they love each other 30 times a day."},{"time":700374,"text":"You just go back and forth:\nyou get angry, you're not angry;"},{"time":703308,"text":"you're angry, you're not angry."},{"time":704855,"text":"But disgust is different."},{"time":706189,"text":"Disgust paints the person\nas subhuman, monstrous,"},{"time":710686,"text":"deformed, morally deformed."},{"time":712519,"text":"Disgust is like indelible ink."},{"time":715768,"text":"There's research from John Gottman\non marital therapy."},{"time":719307,"text":"If you look at the faces -- if one\nof the couple shows disgust or contempt,"},{"time":724456,"text":"that's a predictor that they're going\nto get divorced soon,"},{"time":727576,"text":"whereas if they show anger,\nthat doesn't predict anything,"},{"time":730499,"text":"because if you deal with anger well,\nit actually is good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":733232,"text":"So this election is different."},{"time":734708,"text":"Donald Trump personally\nuses the word \"disgust\" a lot."},{"time":738386,"text":"He's very germ-sensitive,\nso disgust does matter a lot --"},{"time":741267,"text":"more for him, that's something\nunique to him --"},{"time":745201,"text":"but as we demonize each other more,"},{"time":748128,"text":"and again, through\nthe Manichaean worldview,"},{"time":751561,"text":"the idea that the world\nis a battle between good and evil"},{"time":754315,"text":"as this has been ramping up,"},{"time":755686,"text":"we're more likely not just to say\nthey're wrong or I don't like them,"},{"time":759036,"text":"but we say they're evil, they're satanic,"},{"time":761596,"text":"they're disgusting, they're revolting."},{"time":763541,"text":"And then we want nothing to do with them."},{"time":766806,"text":"And that's why I think we're seeing it,\nfor example, on campus now."},{"time":770317,"text":"We're seeing more the urge\nto keep people off campus,"},{"time":772981,"text":"silence them, keep them away."},{"time":774950,"text":"I'm afraid that this whole\ngeneration of young people,"},{"time":777569,"text":"if their introduction to politics\ninvolves a lot of disgust,"},{"time":781386,"text":"they're not going to want to be involved\nin politics as they get older."}]},{"cues":[{"time":785506,"text":"CA: So how do we deal with that?"},{"time":787370,"text":"Disgust. How do you defuse disgust?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":792874,"text":"JH: You can't do it with reasons."},{"time":795312,"text":"I think ..."},{"time":798257,"text":"I studied disgust for many years,\nand I think about emotions a lot."},{"time":801498,"text":"And I think that the opposite\nof disgust is actually love."},{"time":805764,"text":"Love is all about, like ..."},{"time":809239,"text":"Disgust is closing off, borders."},{"time":811834,"text":"Love is about dissolving walls."},{"time":815074,"text":"So personal relationships, I think,"},{"time":817578,"text":"are probably the most\npowerful means we have."},{"time":821291,"text":"You can be disgusted by a group of people,"},{"time":824012,"text":"but then you meet a particular person"},{"time":825954,"text":"and you genuinely discover\nthat they're lovely."},{"time":828754,"text":"And then gradually that chips away\nor changes your category as well."},{"time":834016,"text":"The tragedy is, Americans used to be\nmuch more mixed up in the their towns"},{"time":840017,"text":"by left-right or politics."},{"time":842175,"text":"And now that it's become\nthis great moral divide,"},{"time":844530,"text":"there's a lot of evidence\nthat we're moving to be near people"},{"time":847697,"text":"who are like us politically."},{"time":849233,"text":"It's harder to find somebody\nwho's on the other side."},{"time":851787,"text":"So they're over there, they're far away."},{"time":854101,"text":"It's harder to get to know them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855695,"text":"CA: What would you say to someone\nor say to Americans,"},{"time":859943,"text":"people generally,"},{"time":861125,"text":"about what we should understand\nabout each other"},{"time":863758,"text":"that might help us rethink for a minute"},{"time":867257,"text":"this \"disgust\" instinct?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":870086,"text":"JH: Yes."},{"time":871262,"text":"A really important\nthing to keep in mind --"},{"time":873439,"text":"there's research by political\nscientist Alan Abramowitz,"},{"time":878179,"text":"showing that American democracy\nis increasingly governed"},{"time":882196,"text":"by what's called \"negative partisanship.\""},{"time":884875,"text":"That means you think,\nOK there's a candidate,"},{"time":888010,"text":"you like the candidate,\nyou vote for the candidate."},{"time":890440,"text":"But with the rise of negative advertising"},{"time":892523,"text":"and social media\nand all sorts of other trends,"},{"time":894771,"text":"increasingly, the way elections are done"},{"time":896836,"text":"is that each side tries to make\nthe other side so horrible, so awful,"},{"time":900841,"text":"that you'll vote for my guy by default."}]},{"cues":[{"time":903319,"text":"And so as we more and more vote\nagainst the other side"},{"time":906313,"text":"and not for our side,"},{"time":907668,"text":"you have to keep in mind\nthat if people are on the left,"},{"time":913199,"text":"they think, \"Well, I used to think\nthat Republicans were bad,"},{"time":916133,"text":"but now Donald Trump proves it."},{"time":917640,"text":"And now every Republican,\nI can paint with all the things"},{"time":920515,"text":"that I think about Trump.\""},{"time":921921,"text":"And that's not necessarily true."},{"time":923538,"text":"They're generally not very happy\nwith their candidate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926254,"text":"This is the most negative partisanship\nelection in American history."},{"time":931860,"text":"So you have to first separate\nyour feelings about the candidate"},{"time":935247,"text":"from your feelings about the people\nwho are given a choice."},{"time":938208,"text":"And then you have to realize that,"},{"time":941246,"text":"because we all live\nin a separate moral world --"},{"time":943690,"text":"the metaphor I use in the book\nis that we're all trapped in \"The Matrix,\""},{"time":947165,"text":"or each moral community is a matrix,\na consensual hallucination."},{"time":950713,"text":"And so if you're within the blue matrix,"},{"time":952980,"text":"everything's completely compelling\nthat the other side --"},{"time":956198,"text":"they're troglodytes, they're racists,\nthey're the worst people in the world,"},{"time":959853,"text":"and you have all the facts\nto back that up."},{"time":961981,"text":"But somebody in the next house from yours"},{"time":964280,"text":"is living in a different moral matrix."},{"time":966337,"text":"They live in a different video game,"},{"time":968308,"text":"and they see a completely\ndifferent set of facts."},{"time":970710,"text":"And each one sees\ndifferent threats to the country."},{"time":973410,"text":"And what I've found\nfrom being in the middle"},{"time":975524,"text":"and trying to understand both sides\nis: both sides are right."},{"time":978475,"text":"There are a lot of threats\nto this country,"},{"time":980619,"text":"and each side is constitutionally\nincapable of seeing them all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984963,"text":"CA: So, are you saying\nthat we almost need a new type of empathy?"},{"time":991506,"text":"Empathy is traditionally framed as:"},{"time":993700,"text":"\"Oh, I feel your pain.\nI can put myself in your shoes.\""},{"time":996415,"text":"And we apply it to the poor,\nthe needy, the suffering."},{"time":1000023,"text":"We don't usually apply it\nto people who we feel as other,"},{"time":1003870,"text":"or we're disgusted by."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1005359,"text":"JH: No. That's right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006534,"text":"CA: What would it look like\nto build that type of empathy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1012268,"text":"JH: Actually, I think ..."},{"time":1014145,"text":"Empathy is a very, very\nhot topic in psychology,"},{"time":1016474,"text":"and it's a very popular word\non the left in particular."},{"time":1019156,"text":"Empathy is a good thing, and empathy\nfor the preferred classes of victims."},{"time":1023180,"text":"So it's important to empathize"},{"time":1024657,"text":"with the groups that we on the left\nthink are so important."},{"time":1027505,"text":"That's easy to do,\nbecause you get points for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1030442,"text":"But empathy really should get you points\nif you do it when it's hard to do."},{"time":1034513,"text":"And, I think ..."},{"time":1036291,"text":"You know, we had a long 50-year period\nof dealing with our race problems"},{"time":1041403,"text":"and legal discrimination,"},{"time":1043682,"text":"and that was our top priority\nfor a long time"},{"time":1045893,"text":"and it still is important."},{"time":1047167,"text":"But I think this year,"},{"time":1048720,"text":"I'm hoping it will make people see"},{"time":1051148,"text":"that we have an existential\nthreat on our hands."},{"time":1053967,"text":"Our left-right divide, I believe,"},{"time":1056658,"text":"is by far the most important\ndivide we face."},{"time":1058842,"text":"We still have issues about race\nand gender and LGBT,"},{"time":1061897,"text":"but this is the urgent need\nof the next 50 years,"},{"time":1065292,"text":"and things aren't going\nto get better on their own."},{"time":1069021,"text":"So we're going to need to do\na lot of institutional reforms,"},{"time":1071880,"text":"and we could talk about that,"},{"time":1073313,"text":"but that's like a whole long,\nwonky conversation."},{"time":1075667,"text":"But I think it starts with people\nrealizing that this is a turning point."},{"time":1079537,"text":"And yes, we need a new kind of empathy."},{"time":1082370,"text":"We need to realize:"},{"time":1083899,"text":"this is what our country needs,"},{"time":1085465,"text":"and this is what you need\nif you don't want to --"},{"time":1087843,"text":"Raise your hand if you want\nto spend the next four years"},{"time":1090562,"text":"as angry and worried as you've been\nfor the last year -- raise your hand."},{"time":1094072,"text":"So if you want to escape from this,"},{"time":1095801,"text":"read Buddha, read Jesus,\nread Marcus Aurelius."},{"time":1097976,"text":"They have all kinds of great advice\nfor how to drop the fear,"},{"time":1103062,"text":"reframe things,"},{"time":1104264,"text":"stop seeing other people as your enemy."},{"time":1106371,"text":"There's a lot of guidance in ancient\nwisdom for this kind of empathy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1109702,"text":"CA: Here's my last question:"},{"time":1111103,"text":"Personally, what can\npeople do to help heal?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1115462,"text":"JH: Yeah, it's very hard to just decide\nto overcome your deepest prejudices."},{"time":1119569,"text":"And there's research showing"},{"time":1121054,"text":"that political prejudices are deeper\nand stronger than race prejudices"},{"time":1125427,"text":"in the country now."},{"time":1127395,"text":"So I think you have to make an effort --\nthat's the main thing."},{"time":1130851,"text":"Make an effort to actually meet somebody."},{"time":1132879,"text":"Everybody has a cousin, a brother-in-law,"},{"time":1135113,"text":"somebody who's on the other side."},{"time":1137006,"text":"So, after this election --"},{"time":1139252,"text":"wait a week or two,"},{"time":1140627,"text":"because it's probably going to feel\nawful for one of you --"},{"time":1143487,"text":"but wait a couple weeks, and then\nreach out and say you want to talk."},{"time":1147663,"text":"And before you do it,"},{"time":1149111,"text":"read Dale Carnegie, \"How to Win\nFriends and Influence People\" --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1152280,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1153343,"text":"I'm totally serious."},{"time":1154534,"text":"You'll learn techniques\nif you start by acknowledging,"},{"time":1157148,"text":"if you start by saying,"},{"time":1158333,"text":"\"You know, we don't agree on a lot,"},{"time":1160027,"text":"but one thing I really respect\nabout you, Uncle Bob,\""},{"time":1162589,"text":"or \"... about you conservatives, is ... \""},{"time":1164672,"text":"And you can find something."},{"time":1166030,"text":"If you start with some\nappreciation, it's like magic."},{"time":1168817,"text":"This is one of the main\nthings I've learned"},{"time":1170955,"text":"that I take into my human relationships."},{"time":1172892,"text":"I still make lots of stupid mistakes,"},{"time":1174836,"text":"but I'm incredibly good\nat apologizing now,"},{"time":1176876,"text":"and at acknowledging what\nsomebody was right about."},{"time":1179317,"text":"And if you do that,"},{"time":1180495,"text":"then the conversation goes really well,\nand it's actually really fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1184717,"text":"CA: Jon, it's absolutely fascinating\nspeaking with you."},{"time":1187386,"text":"It really does feel like\nthe ground that we're on"},{"time":1191168,"text":"is a ground populated by deep questions\nof morality and human nature."},{"time":1196366,"text":"Your wisdom couldn't be more relevant."},{"time":1198814,"text":"Thank you so much for sharing\nthis time with us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1201133,"text":"JH: Thanks, Chris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1202309,"text":"JH: Thanks, everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1203494,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}